type PayoutSpecificFeatures: <"....">  // FORK_2
        [metadata key]

    knockEvent KnockEvent (0..*) <"Represents the functional operation [ F(X,In) = X * (Boolean) ] or the functional operation [ F(X,Out) = X * (1 - Boolean) ] where : [In] or [Out] designates the knockType, [Boolean] equals [1] when the event trigger has occurred, else equals [0] ; and [X] is the object for which this attribute is defined. As an indication, this feature shall also be used for defining any kinds of corridor structure which involves two trigger events: one being the upper barrier and the second one being the lower barrier of the corridor structure.">
        [metadata reference]
    capFloor CapFloor (0..*) <"Represents the functional operation [ F(X,Cap) = min(X,Cap) ] or the functional operation [ F(X,Floor) = max(X,Floor) ] where : [Cap] or [Floor] is the numerical value of the barrier level, either a price or a quantity ; and [X] is the value of the object for which this attribute is defined.">
        [metadata reference]
    averaging Averaging (0..1) <"Represents the functional operation [ F(X) = MeanType(X(*)) ] where : [MeanType] is either Arithmetic or Geometirc or Harmonic type of averaging, [X(*)] being a collection of multiple objects e.g. X1, X2,...,Xn for instance multiple observables (e.g. basket consituents) or multiple observation dates related to one given observable ; and [X] is the value of the object for which this attribute is defined.">
        [metadata reference]
    ranking Ranking (0..1) <"Represents the functional operation [ F(X,Min) = Nth(*)(X(*)) ] or [ F(X,Max) = Nth(*)(X(*)) ] where : [Nth(*)] designate at least one or multiple ranks for selecting respectively one or more values with regards to [X(*)] being a collection of multiple objects e.g. X1, X2,...,Xn for instance multiple observables (e.g. basket consituents) or multiple observation dates related to one given observable, [Min] and [Max] indicating the ranking direction when selecting the values (e.g. selecting the 4th and the 2nd worst values, for instance, would be represented by: rankingDirection=Min, nthRank=4, nthRanknth=2) ; and [X] is the value of the object for which this attribute is defined. The ranking feature is notably used for representing Worst Of or Best Of (when one unique value is selected: either last one or first rank, respectively) but also for representing more sophisticated types such as Rainbow features (when multiple values are selected e.g. 1st, 2nd 3rd, etc. usually with a particular weighting per rank).">
        [metadata reference]
    multiplier Leverage (0..*) <"Represents the functional operation [ F(X) = X * N ] or the functional operation [ F(X) = X / D ] where: [N] is a Numerator value, [D] is a Denominator value ; and [X] is the value of the object for which this attribute is defined. If any, multiple instances represent a straight concatenation of such operations e.g. say n+m attributes would be populated: numerator [N1], Numerator [N2], ..., Numerator [Nn] exist, also possiby with Denominator [D1], Denominator [D2], ..., Denominator [Dm] then this would represent [ F(X) = X * N1 * N2 * ... * Nn * 1/D1 * 1/D2 * ... * 1/Dm ]."> // FORK_2
        [metadata reference]
    quantityCumulation QuantityCumulation (0..1) <"Specifies cumulation dates i.e. dates on which a given quantity is incremented over time. As an indication, products for which such feature is used are often referred to as Accumulator or Decumulator.">
        [metadata reference]
    compoundedFeature PayoutSpecificFeatures (0..1) <"Represents the compounding of multiple features. As an indication, considering the nesting structure of the modelisation tree from left-to-right provides a direct representation of the compounding order based on which features shall be applied for any calculation purposes.">
        [metadata reference]
    algebraicOperator AlgebraicOperator (0..1) // Fork_2

type KnockEvent: <"Represents the functional operation [ F(X,In) = X * (Boolean) ] or the functional operation [ F(X,Out) = X * (1 - Boolean) ] where : [In] or [Out] designates the knockType, [Boolean] equals [1] when the triggerCondition is verified as true, else equals [0], and [X] is the value of the object for which KnockCondition is defined as an attribute. Accordingly, this specifies that the existence of the parent object for which KnockBarrier is defined as an attribute is contigent, either because it does not exists until the condition is verified as true, which is defined as the Knock-In type, or because it does exist unless the condition is verified as true, which is defined as the Knock-Out type. As an indication, this feature shall also be used for defining any kinds of corridor structure which involves two trigger events: one being the upper barrier and the second one being the lower barrier of the corridor structure."> // FORK_2
    [metadata key]

    bespokeExpression BespokeExpression (0..1) <"Any bespoke name or description that may be specified.">
    knockType KnockTypeEnum (1..1) <"Designates the type of barrier: either  [In] or [Out] in the funtional operation [ F(X,In) = X x (Boolean) ] or the functional operation [ F(X,Out) = X x (1 - Boolean) ] where [Boolean] equals [1] when the triggerCondition is verified as true, else equals [0], and [X] is the value of the object for which KnockBarrier is defined as an attribute.">
    referenceObservable NewObservable (0..1) <"Specifies the object to be observed for a price, it could be an asset or a reference.">
        [metadata reference]
    referenceObservablePriceType PriceTypeEnum (0..1) <"Provides enumerated values for types of prices in order to explain how to interpret it and use it in calculations.">
    knockDeterminationMethod DeterminationMethodEnum (1..1)
    knockDeterminationDay ObservationDates (1..2) <"Specifies the dates on which the observable price shall be observed. As an indication, the cardinality permits to populate two instances - based on some conditions - for representing typical use case where the observable price is not only the price for given observation day but is also the price of the prior observation day.">
    knockValuationTime TimeTypeEnum (1..1)
    triggerEvent EventTrigger (1..*) <"Specifies the criteria for determining whether the KnockBarrier is activated or not. As an indication, the cardinality permits to populate multiple instances (typicall use case is for defining a corridor structure which involves two instances : one knock level being the upper barrier and the second one being the lower barrier).">
        [metadata address]
    calculatedValue CalculationValue (0..1) <"The numerical value or dated value which corresponds to the resolved value of the parent object for which this attribute is populated.">
        [metadata reference]
    multipleTriggerCompoundingRule LogicalOperationEnum (0..1)

    condition KnockDeterminationDay: <"For avoiding two schedule date series defined in parallel, being possibly inconsistent between them, the condition ensures that at least one of the two dates is a relative date, meaning that at least one will anchor the other date schedule series, if any.">
        if knockDeterminationDay count = 2
        then knockDeterminationDay -> relativeDate count >= 1

    condition MultipleEvent:
        if triggerEvent count > 1 
        then multipleTriggerCompoundingRule exists 
        else multipleTriggerCompoundingRule is absent

 //   condition KnockReference: <"The first part and the second part of the condition avoids duplicating the knockReference in both knockEvent and triggerEvent levels by implementing a required choice between their respective attributes. As an exception, the third part of the condition is permitting having knockReference in both knockEvent and triggerEvent levels in one particular case that is when the knockReference is a basket (indeed, it is possible in such case to cumulate in consistent manner knockReference attribute related to the basket considered from a net standpoint, together with granular knockReference attributes related to each basketConstituent considered each from an individual standpoint). "> // FORK_2 
    
  //          (referenceObservable exists or referenceCompositeObservable exists)
    //            and (triggerEvent-> referenceObservable is absent and triggerEvent-> referenceCompositeObservable is absent)
      //  or 
        //    (triggerEvent-> referenceObservable exists or triggerEvent-> referenceCompositeObservable exists)
          //      and (referenceObservable is absent and referenceCompositeObservable is absent)
  //      or 
    //        (referenceObservable -> basket exists and triggerEvent-> referenceObservable -> basket exists)
      //          and (triggerEvent -> referenceCompositeObservable is absent and referenceCompositeObservable is absent)
//
   // condition ReferenceObservablePriceType:
  //      if referenceObservablePriceType exists 
    //    then referenceObservable exists 

type EventTrigger : <"Specifies the criteria for determining whether the KnockBarrier is activated or not i.e. the triggerLevel as well as the triggerRule which shall specify the relation between the observable value and the triggerLevel value."> // FORK_2
        [metadata key]
    
    bespokeExpression BespokeExpression (0..1)
    triggerLevel ObservablePriceQuantity (1..1) <"The value of the trigger level.">
    triggerRule TriggerTypeEnum (1..1) <"Specifies the criteria for determining whether the triggerLevel is deemed to have been knocked or not by the observable value.">
    calculatedValue DatedValue (0..1) <"The results of the KnockConditions assessments may be recorded as datedValue series with only boolean values i.e. either 0 or 1 per each date.">
        [metadata reference]
    referenceObservable NewObservable (0..1) <"Specifies the object to be observed for a price, it could be an asset or a reference.">
        [metadata reference]
    referenceObservablePriceType PriceTypeEnum (0..1) <"Provides enumerated values for types of prices in order to explain how to interpret it and use it in calculations.">

    condition CalculationResult:<"The results of the KnockConditions assessments may be recorded as datedValue series with only boolean values i.e. either 0 or 1 per each date.">
        if calculatedValue exists
        then calculatedValue -> value = 0 or calculatedValue -> value = 1

    condition ReferenceObservablePriceType:
        if referenceObservablePriceType exists 
        then referenceObservable exists 

type CapFloor : <"Represents the functional operation [ F(X,Cap) = min(X,Cap) ] or the functional operation [ F(X,Floor) = max(X,Floor) ] where : [Cap] or [Floor] is the value of the barrier level for the given barrierType i.e. Cap or Floor and [X] is the value of the object for which CapFloor is defined as an attribute."> // FORK_2
        [metadata key]
    
